Day 1 Introduction - HTML, CSS, Version Control

	HTML
		Markup Language for the web

		Example:

			Simple HTML Elements

			<h1> Hello World! </h1>  <---- Header with opening tag, intter text, and closing tag

			<a href = "https://www.google.com">
			Link to Google
			</A>

								href is atrribute key
								in "" is attribute value

			Nested HTML Elements

			<ul class = "list pretty-list" id="my-list">
			<Li onclick="do-sth"> One </li>
			<li onclick = "do-sth"> Two </li>
			</ul>

								** ul is list I think


		HTML Document
			Stored in *.html files
			Common Structure
				<!DOCTYPE html>
				<html>
					<head>
						...
					</head>  <--- metadata
					<body>
					...
					</body>  
				</html>


				Metadata: Hidden info about page


