	Common Tags on Moodle
	
	Inline Styling

		Style Atrribute
			<e1 style = "...."> Styled ELement </e1>   *el doesn't exist is any element
														*... is code example 2

		Problem: Repeated code, hard to debug

		Solution: CSS

		HTML link to *.css file:
			<link rel="stylesheet" href="link/to/css/file">

		CSS syntax:

			slector {
				style-1: value;
				style-2: value;
			}


	Important HTML atrributes for styling:
		class :common identification for many elements
			<el class="class-1 class-2...class-n"
				Element 1
			</el>

			<el class="class-1 class-4...class-n"
				Element 2
			</el>

		id :unique identification for an element

	Selectors
		Tag Selector
			tag-name{...}
		Class selector
			.class-name{...}
		ID selector
			#unique-id{...}
		Attribute Selector
			selector[attrKey="attrVal"]
		Child selector (use sparingly)
			selector-1 > selector 2 > ... slector-n {...}
		Descendant selector (avoid)
			selector 1 selector 2 ... selector-n{...}


	The Box Model:
		Every element is contained in a rectangle
			<body>
				<div>
					<h1></h1>h1>
					<p></p>
				</div>
			</body>

		Controls how elements are positioned and interact with each other
		Code example 4


	Positioning
		CSS position rule dictates position relative to document

		static (default)
		relative
			positioned usting top, left, right, bottom - relative to static positioon
			elements inside are positioned relative to parent
		absolute
			positioned relative to first non-static ancestor element
		fixed
			positioned relative to the browser window
		float
			pushed as far possible left or right
			text can wrap arond it
			float is defined as a seperate property from position (float: right, float: left)



