Day 3 JavaScript

	variable declaration
		var x = <value>;

		== doesn't compare types 
		=== also checks types

		us const and let (check those two words on slides) instead of var

		Object declaration
			var x {
				key 1: value1,
				key2: value2
				...
				keyN: valueN
			};
			
		Object Retrieval
			x.key1 -> value1

		Object update
			x.key1 = newValue

		This keyword
			this refers to the object itself	




